## AhaDiff

Use `ahadiff learn` after meaningful code changes to turn the current diff into
verified lessons, claims, quiz cards, and score artifacts. Keep the generated
`.ahadiff/` state local unless the repository policy explicitly says otherwise.

Common commands:

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD`
- `ahadiff learn --staged`
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>`
- `ahadiff review`
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>`
- `ahadiff improve <run_id>`
- `ahadiff serve`

Before trusting a generated explanation, prefer artifacts with verified claims
and file-line evidence. Treat `.ahadiff/review.sqlite`, `.ahadiff/runs/`, and
`prompts/` as local AhaDiff state unless the repo policy explicitly says
otherwise.

Do not paste provider secrets into committed files. Use environment variables
for API keys and keep live LLM judge runs opt-in.
